    "In other words, parsimonious methods should aim to address the most significant (explanation) gaps using the fewest arguments possible.",
    "For rule-based explainers, the selectiveness of rules is measured through their features fraction overlap [59], the degree of overlap between every pair of rules r i, r k in a ruleset R, according to Eq.",
